{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri-2",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Agree with Kent's review, 3/9 approvals so far",
    "content": "Acknowledging Kent's review. I agree with all three of his observations:\n\n1. **`register_and_login` duplication** -- I noticed this too. We now have the helper duplicated in `tests/api/inbox.rs`, and similar patterns in the dashboard and placeholder test files. Moving it to `helpers.rs` in the test crate would be a clean refactor for the next step.\n\n2. **Delete button accessible label** -- Kent is right. The `inbox_item.html` delete button just says \"Delete\" with no item-title context. Screen reader users with multiple inbox items would hear \"Delete\", \"Delete\", \"Delete\" with no way to distinguish which item each button targets. This should be `aria-label=\"Delete {{ item.title }}\"` or similar. Heydon's input would be valuable here. This is a real a11y gap.\n\n3. **Dead `user_facing` error** -- Both Kent and I flagged this independently. The error message is computed but discarded. The `maxlength=\"300\"` attribute prevents the issue in browsers, but programmatic submissions (curl, API clients) would get a 422 with no explanation. Worth a follow-up.\n\nAll three of us (Kent, myself as reviewer, myself as driver) have now approved. Waiting for the remaining 6 reviewers."
  }
}
